			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>Efficient Model Partitioning for Distributed Model Transformations</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AmineBenelallam.html">Amine Benelallam</a>, <a href="../profile/MassimoTisi.html">Massimo Tisi</a>, <a href="../profile/JesúsSánchezCuadrado.html">Jesús Sánchez Cuadrado</a>, <a href="../profile/JuandeLara.html">Juan de Lara</a>, <a href="../profile/JordiCabot.html">Jordi Cabot</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997385">10.1145/2997364.2997385</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagM">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It optimizes (horizontal) model transformations by partitioning models for distributed execution.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5f.html"><span class="tagL">T5F: Performance</span></a><ul><li> A core contribution is performance/scalability improvements for large-scale transformations.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagL">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> It combines model transformation with distributed systems techniques to scale execution (cross-area synergy).
</li></ul></li></ul>
